    h3.govuk-heading-l.util_mt-medium id="intro" Introduction

    p Help with fees makes it possible for people who aren't able to pay their court or tribunal fee to get financial help. Applicants are assessed on the basis of their financial situation.

    p As you process an application for help with fees, you'll see prompts and explanations on the right hand side of the screen. You can also return to this page if you need more help.

    p If you need more information than is in this guide, see the #{link_to 'Staff guidance ', 'https://intranet.justice.gov.uk/about-hmcts/my-work/help-with-fees/staff-guidance/', target: '_blank'}

    p The service has a link to the Department for Work and Pensions and can check whether applicants are receiving benefits.

    p When you’ve entered all the information from the form you’ll get a result about whether the applicant is eligible for help with fees.

    p In some cases you may be prompted to send a letter requesting further information or part-payment if the applicant has to pay part of the fee.

    h4.govuk-heading-m Use Firefox web browser

    p Using Firefox will give you the best experience. You can set up a Firefox desktop shortcut by doing the following:
    ol.govuk-list.govuk-list--number
      li right click on your desktop
      li select New > Shortcut
      li paste the following line, including all punctuation, into the Location field and click Next: "C:\Program Files\Mozilla Firefox\firefox.exe" https://staff.helpwithcourtfees.service.gov.uk/
      li in the Name field, select firefox.exe and replace it with 'Help with fees'
      li click finish

    br
    h3.govuk-heading-l id="who-apply" Who can apply for help with fees?
    h4.govuk-heading-m Individuals can apply for help with fees if they:
    ul.govuk-list.govuk-list--bullet
      li have no savings and investments or only a small amount
      li and receive certain benefits
      li or are on a low income

    h3.govuk-heading-l id="before-start" Before you start
    h4.govuk-heading-m Check the statement of truth has been signed and the form has been completed.
    p We have introduced a free text box for appellants to fill in if they are applying on the basis of income but have declared £0 income. It asks them how they support themselves and aims to reduce incorrectly completed income statements.
    p Unsigned or incomplete forms must be returned to the applicant.
    h4.govuk-heading-m Legal Aid
    p If the applicant is getting Legal Aid, check if they're eligible to apply for help with fees.

